The fan electrical input power (FEP
act
) in kilowatts must be determined at every duty point specified by the manufacturer in accordance with one of the test methods listed in Table 1, and the following sections of AMCA 214-21: Section 2, âReferences (Normative)â; Section 7, âTesting,â including the referenced provisions to AMCA 210-16 and ISO 5801:2017 as listed in sections 2.2.2 and 2.2.3 of this appendix; Section 8.1, âLaboratory Measurement Onlyâ (as applicable); and Annex J, âOther data and calculations to be retained.â

The FEI must be determined at every duty point in accordance with Section 4, âCalculation of the FEI for a single duty point,â and Section 5, âReference Fan Electrical Power (FEP
